                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.75 National Telephone Company/38:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from"
                            >Laughlin</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-22T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 22, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 22—11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>88. Tour 99, and my 87. Though I communicated your representations completely and
                    in the most serious manner and actually left with <persName corresp="#p_AM1"
                        >Azaña</persName> the memorandum I had made to assist me in exactitude at
                    the interview, it occurs to me to ask if you wish me to emphasize your position
                    still further by a formal note to the Foreign Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
